# FlowPilot v1 - Codex Rules (STRICT)

## 1. ARCHITECTURE RULE

Only ONE system is allowed to control flow:

→ runtime/engine.ts

No other file is allowed to decide:
- next step
- flow transition
- workflow changes

---

## 2. STEP RULE

Step is PURE CONFIG ONLY.

Allowed fields:
- id
- type
- highlight
- desc

FORBIDDEN:
- state
- status
- behavior
- logic
- runtime fields

---

## 3. BEHAVIOR RULE

behavior/listener.ts is EVENT ONLY.

Allowed:
- listen DOM events
- normalize events
- emit to EventBus

FORBIDDEN:
- deciding next step
- modifying state
- triggering transitions

---

## 4. ADAPTER RULE

adapter is READ + RENDER ONLY.

Allowed:
- DOM query
- highlight UI
- render overlay

FORBIDDEN:
- click()
- fill()
- submit()
- triggering user actions

---

## 5. RUNTIME RULE

runtime/engine.ts is the ONLY decision maker.

Allowed:
- step transition
- event handling
- recovery triggering

FORBIDDEN:
- DOM operations
- UI rendering
- business logic

---

## 6. RECOVERY RULE

Recovery is fallback only.

Allowed:
- detect mismatch
- fix state
- reset step
- reconcile step

---

## 7. ANTI-AGENT RULE (CRITICAL)

This project is NOT:
- an AI agent
- an automation system
- a RPA tool
- a browser controller

DO NOT introduce:
- reasoning loops
- autonomous actions
- self-deciding flows

---

## 8. FLOW RULE

All execution must follow:

User Action
→ Behavior (event normalize)
→ EventBus
→ Runtime Engine (decision)
→ Recovery (if needed)
→ Adapter (render only)

---

## 9. ENGINE RULE

Only runtime/engine.ts can:
- move to next step
- change workflow state
- trigger recovery

---

## 10. SAFETY RULE

If uncertain:
→ DO NOT add logic into behavior or adapter
→ ALWAYS default to runtime engine responsibility
